addComputeUnits(bytes32,bytes32[]).details: Add compute units to a peer

changeMinPricePerCuPerEpoch(bytes32,uint.details: Change the min price per CU per epoch of an offer

changePaymentToken(bytes32,address).details: Change the payment token of an offer

getComputeUnitIds(bytes32).details: Returns the compute unit ids of a peer

getComputeUnits(bytes32).details: Returns the compute units info of a peer

matchDeal(address,bytes32[],bytes32[][][.details: Match Deal with Compute Units provided.There should be `bytes32[][] calldata peers` as well, but it is not supported by subgraph codegen.Ref to https://github.com/graphprotocol/graph-tooling/issues/342.

params.computeUnits: : Compute Units per offer id (3D array: provider -> peer -> CU) to match with.
params.offers: : Offers array that represents offers in computeUnits 3D array.

params.minPricePerCuPerEpoch: The min price per CU per epoch which the provider specify for the matching with the deal
params.paymentToken: The payment token of the offer
params.peers: The compute peers of the offer

removeComputePeer(bytes32).details: Remove compute peers from an offer after all CUs removed.Only owner can remove Peer.

removeComputeUnit(bytes32).details: Remove compute units from a peer.Only owner can remove Compute Unit that not in Deal and in CC.

removeEffectorInfo((bytes4,bytes32)).details: Remove the effector info. Effector info can be removed by the contract owner

removeOffer(bytes32).details: Remove an offer.Only owner can change offer after all Peers removed (and CUs before).

setEffectorInfo((bytes4,bytes32),string,.details: Set the effector info. Effector info can be added by the contract owner

matchDeal(address,bytes32[],bytes32[][][.notice: Match deal with offers and compute units (peers checks through compute units).It validates provided CUs and silently ignore unvalidated ones on checking:- deal.maxWorkersPerProvider and silently ignore other CUs out of this limit.- Offer, or Peer not allowed to match (deal.isProviderAllowed, allowed prices, paymentToken, effectors)- Compute Unit (CU): Active CC status, also note, protocol does not allow more than one worker per peerfor the same Deal. But, when deal consists of whitelisted provider - CUs of this Providercould be matched without even CC.TODO: consolidate workaround: when it comes to check CC status, on wrong status the whole transactionwill be failed instead of to be silenced.This method is mirrored in ts-client/src/dealMatcherClient/dealMatcherClient.ts.
